Excellent. Step 14 is one of the most important steps in the entire Linux roadmap.

This is the step that separates someone who knows Linux commands from someone who can solve production incidents.

In companies like Amazon, Google, Microsoft, Adobe, Oracle, Walmart, Atlassian, and Flipkart, 70–80% of a DevOps/SRE engineer's daily work is troubleshooting production issues, not writing commands.

