Practical Lab (90–120 Minutes)
Scenario 1 – Nginx Service Down
Stop Nginx:
sudo systemctl stop nginx
Verify:
systemctl status nginx
Start it.
Confirm it is serving traffic.
Scenario 2 – Disk Full

Create a large test file:

fallocate -l 1G test.img

Check:

df -h

Delete it and verify recovered space.

Scenario 3 – High CPU

Start a CPU-intensive process:

yes > /dev/null

Monitor:

top

Stop the process:

kill PID
Scenario 4 – Memory Usage

Run a memory-intensive application in a lab environment.

Observe:

free -h

Monitor:

vmstat
Scenario 5 – SSH Issue

Stop SSH:

sudo systemctl stop ssh

Observe connection failure from another terminal.

Restart:

sudo systemctl start ssh
Scenario 6 – Log Investigation

View SSH logs:

journalctl -u ssh

Search for failed login attempts.

