🎯 Mentor's Advice

The best SREs don't memorize hundreds of commands—they follow a disciplined process.

Whenever an incident occurs, remember this checklist:

Understand the problem.
Collect evidence.
Check system health (CPU, memory, disk, network).
Verify services.
Read logs.
Identify the root cause.
Apply the fix.
Confirm the service is healthy.
Document the incident.
Implement preventive measures.

Following this workflow will make you more effective during production incidents and is exactly the mindset interviewers look for in DevOps and SRE roles.

